Name: Itchan Kala
Description: Itchan Kala - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Walled inner town of Khiva with well-preserved Islamic architecture and historic monuments.

Name: Historic Centre of Bukhara
Description: Historic Centre of Bukhara - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Ancient city center reflecting over two millennia of history as a major center of Islamic culture.

Name: Historic Centre of Shakhrisyabz
Description: Historic Centre of Shakhrisyabz - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Birthplace of Amir Timur with monuments from the Timurid period.

Name: Samarkand – Crossroad of Cultures
Description: Samarkand – Crossroad of Cultures - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Historic town exemplifying a crossroad of world cultures along the Silk Road.

Name: Silk Roads: Zarafshan-Karakum Corridor
Description: Silk Roads: Zarafshan-Karakum Corridor - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Key section of the Silk Roads connecting Central Asia with 31 component sites.

Name: Western Tien-Shan
Description: Western Tien-Shan - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Transnational mountain range with exceptional biodiversity.

Name: Cold Winter Deserts of Turan
Description: Cold Winter Deserts of Turan - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Unique desert ecosystem with exceptional biodiversity.
